sellerAgent.name: Another Fine Home By Robbie and Elaine

data.description: Introducing this stunning showpiece, filled with elevated character and thoughtful design. Located in the highly sought-after, award winning Forsyth County school district! This immaculately maintained 6-bedroom, 4.5-bathroom home, features incredible upgrades throughout. Two spacious master suites, one on the lower floor, and one on the upper floor, both with over-sized walk-in closets. Each master bath is luxuriously appointed with deep soaking jetted tubs, double sinks, granite topped vanities, large walk-in/glass enclosed shower and wood plantation shutters.   The open concept, gourmet kitchen is truly the heart of this home! Newer stainless-steel appliances, hood vent over gas cook top, convection capable double ovens, granite counters, large custom island w/beadboard kick area, recessed lighting, abundant room in cabinets & soft close drawers. Unique kitchen features include hidden slide out spice rack storage and a skylight overhead! Walk-in pantry w/wood shelving. Real hardwood floors throughout the main level, lower level and upstairs hallway. Brand new, plush carpeting in upstairs bedrooms and new Berber stair runners. The laundry room has a custom storage cabinet w/granite top, additional wall mounted cabinets, and a utility sink. Secondary upper-level bedroom highlights collectively include, ensuite bath access, privacy pocket door, board & batten accent wall w/ledge, a play loft with ladder, and a fun "Georgia Room" complete with "G" logo custom carpet and chalk paint accent wall. Additional highlights include: TWO 3.5-ton HVAC units, dual NEST Smart thermostats, faux wood blinds, upgraded baseboards and crown molding, custom built-in bookshelves on main level, premium brand (Kohler, Hunter, Delta, Hampton Bay, etc.) faucets, toilets, fans & fixtures, Pella brand glass sliding door, and flooring in the attic for easy access. Extremely energy efficient and insulated!   The lower-level family room has a gorgeous, whitewashed stone wall surrounding the fireplace. Large two car garage offers a convenient second laundry area and side door access to attached storage room. Expansive deck with outdoor kitchen (Big Green Egg) and steps leading to a netted walk-on trampoline as well as a cozy fire pit area. Fully fenced large backyard and plenty of green space for play or gardening. Pest resistant cedar siding. This .5-acre home has it all! Nestled at the end of the street in a family friendly neighborhood, very near the South end of Lake Lanier. Minutes to GA-400, Northside Hospital, shopping and dining. Come and see for yourself, today!
